         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Nasova. Fiji ¶ 4th November 1881 ¶ My dear Sir, ¶  ¶ Presuming upon your kindness I take the liberty of enclosing a leaf (or frond) from a Fern received by me this morning from a person who collects f...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.11.04</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From John Thurston</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M76, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Nasova. Fiji</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">4th November 1881</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Presuming upon your kindness I take the liberty of enclosing a leaf (or frond) from a Fern received by me this morning from a person who collects for me — hap-hazard. Two mails are leaving tonight one for Melbourne and one for New Zealand and consequently I have no time to look at it. Not having seen it before, during a 16 years residence in the South Seas, I send it on to you in case it may be something new —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I recently was visited by a young German Carl Weber who brought me letters from the German Consul in Sydney, an old friend of mine.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I sent Mr Weber on with letters to the [Rotho]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ratu?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>— or Chief of Thakandrovi<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thakundrove Peninsula, Vanua Levu Island?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(who was educated by me) and set him exploring the lake region of Taveuni which island reaches an altitude of 4040 feet. The lake is 2500 feet above the level of the sea. I have given him letters to my people there so that he can explore to his hearts content and live at free quarters. He is, I understand, chiefly interested in the lower forms of vegetation. I enclose a note from him announcing his arrival.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Note not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Perhaps you might like to know of his presence here.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Believe me</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>my dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>very faithfully yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>John B. Thurston.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Pray excuse signs of haste.</p>
         </div>
